From 8a837ff645ae2bf4d0e1d5f316b44731c9a64a9d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 17:04:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(slayzone): windowless tab panes + visible
 extension-management window
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Severs the per-task Browser's window-ness from its tab-hood so extensions
(1Password) install and work without stray/closable windows.

- SlayzoneHiddenBrowserView: the embedded-tab host's Browsers reuse the real
  BrowserView but no-op Show/Activate/etc. — they hold extension-capable tabs
  composited into the shell slot and NEVER surface an OS window (install /
  window.open / target=_blank no longer pop a closable window that kills the
  pane). browser_window_factory routes the embedded-tab marker to it.
- Extension-management window: a NORMAL, VISIBLE Chrome window (kExtensionsBrowser
  marker → plain BrowserView) on the shared profile, 80% centered, opened to the
  Web Store via the "slayzone:open-extensions" CreateView sentinel. The install
  flow needs a TABBED visible window to anchor its prompt
  (extension_install_ui_desktop.cc), which a hidden pane can't provide — so
  management gets its own real window; installs land in the shared profile and
  apply to the panes. Themed dark + the SlayZone accent (#7c7cf0) so it reads as
  ours.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
